'''WED Treadwell repair droids''' was a line of [[maintenance droid]]s manufactured by [[Cybot Galactica]] that came in a range of models.

==Characteristics==
[[File:CashOut-AtG.png|thumb|left|220px|A Jawa with a WED-15 Septoid Treadwell.]]
WED Treadwells were flexible<ref name="Droids">''[[Star Wars Builders: Droids]]''</ref> [[Class five droid|class 5]]<ref name="Droidography" /> utility and [[Maintenance droid|repair droids]]. Standing at around a [[meter]] tall, they came in a range of models, but all had a flat,<ref name="WED Treadwell Droid" /> wide treaded base,<ref name="Droids" /> a spindly,<ref name="WED Treadwell Droid" /> telescopic stalk, upon which was mounted binocular [[Photoreceptor|visual sensors]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> WEDs also had a cluster of [[Limb|arms]] tipped with various tools,<ref name="WED Treadwell Droid" /> which could be purchased separately. Treadwells were used to repair [[Starship|ships]], machinery, and other droids, but were relativity fragile and required frequent maintenance.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> Despite this, they had the ability to keep working at optimal capacity until they were destroyed.<ref name="Force Arena">''[[Star Wars: Force Arena]]''</ref>

There were four known models:

*[[WED-15 Treadwell droid]]<ref name="Droidography" />
*[[WED-15 Septoid Treadwell]]<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" />
*[[WED 15 "Septoid 2" Treadwell toolkit droid]]<ref name="CL2016">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref>
*[[WED-15-XT Treadwell droid]]<ref name="CVDNE">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]''</ref>

==History==
Manufactured by [[Cybot Galactica]],<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> WED Treadwell repair droids were commonly<ref name="Droids" /> found throughout [[the galaxy]],<ref name="WED Treadwell Droid" /> just as helpful on a [[moisture farm]] as they were in a starship [[hangar]].<ref name="Droids" />

WED Treadwells were used by both sides of the [[Galactic Civil War]]; the [[Galactic Empire]] used them to repair their turrets and structures,<ref name="Force Arena" /> while the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]] used them to make field repairs to vehicles in the heat of combat.<ref name="Commander">''[[Star Wars: Force Commander]]''</ref>

